WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.900
Alright, let's talk about money.

2
00:00:02.760 --> 00:00:06.080
Specifically, how your performance turns
into a paycheck.

3
00:00:07.020 --> 00:00:10.700
I'm going to lay out how compensation works
here so there's no mystery about it.

4
00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:11.360
The more you

5
00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:16.140
understand this, the clearer the connection
between your daily work and what you earn.

6
00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:21.680
Whatever seat you're in, compensation here
is built around the same idea.

7
00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:24.460
A base while you ramp up,

8
00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:30.500
performance pay on the results your role
owns, and bonuses for hitting milestones along

9
00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:31.040
the way.

10
00:00:32.120 --> 00:00:36.380
When you start, you receive a base rate
while you're ramping up.

11
00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:38.980
You're learning, building skills,

12
00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:41.220
getting comfortable with the process.

13
00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:44.460
The base pay makes sure you've got income
coming in while

14
00:00:44.460 --> 00:00:46.080
you're still getting up to speed.

15
00:00:46.540 --> 00:00:49.900
Once you're consistently hitting your role's
KPIs, you

16
00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:52.180
graduate to the full performance structure.

17
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:54.060
That's the transition point.

18
00:00:55.440 --> 00:00:56.740
Take the lead sourcing seat

19
00:00:56.740 --> 00:01:01.440
as an example. You earn a commission on every
deal that closes where you are the person

20
00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:01.690
who

21
00:01:01.690 --> 00:01:03.300
sourced and qualified the lead.

22
00:01:03.380 --> 00:01:04.860
You did the follow-up.

23
00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:06.700
You built the relationship.

24
00:01:07.020 --> 00:01:07.270
You

25
00:01:07.270 --> 00:01:12.380
handed it off with a clean, complete package
and the acquisition team closed it.

26
00:01:12.580 --> 00:01:13.600
That's your deal.

27
00:01:14.580 --> 00:01:17.740
And performance pay moves with your
performance.

28
00:01:18.660 --> 00:01:20.680
Strong months show up in your paycheck.

29
00:01:22.320 --> 00:01:25.480
Milestone bonuses work the same way in every
seat.

30
00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:27.460
They count on real outcomes.

31
00:01:28.020 --> 00:01:28.860
In lead sourcing,

32
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:32.720
an appointment counts when the seller actually
shows up for the call, not when you put

33
00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:33.180
it on the

34
00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:37.000
calendar. Real results, not activity for its
own sake.

35
00:01:38.140 --> 00:01:40.580
The math is direct. The better you get at

36
00:01:40.580 --> 00:01:42.420
your craft, the more you make.

37
00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.440
And good work has a long tail.

38
00:01:46.280 --> 00:01:48.160
Deals you worked months ago can still

39
00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:52.680
close and that follow-through is exactly
what gets noticed and rewarded here.

40
00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:55.080
The people who earn the

41
00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:58.700
most here aren't necessarily the ones with
the most raw volume.

42
00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:00.520
They're the ones who are thorough,

43
00:02:01.020 --> 00:02:04.600
consistent, and don't let good leads die
from neglect.

44
00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.420
More quality conversations means more

45
00:02:07.420 --> 00:02:08.540
deals in your pipeline.

46
00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:14.260
Consistent follow-up means those deals
actually convert instead of going cold.

47
00:02:14.620 --> 00:02:20.040
And clean handoffs mean the acquisition team
can close efficiently instead of scrambling

48
00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:20.300
for

49
00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:26.100
missing information. Every lead you let slip
is potential commission you left on the

50
00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:26.440
table.

51
00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:30.500
Every thorough handoff is money you're
putting in your own pocket.

52
00:02:30.600 --> 00:02:34.560
It's that direct. Now, your exact

53
00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:39.860
numbers, your base rate, how your performance
pay is calculated, your bonus milestones,

54
00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:40.660
those live in

55
00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:42.420
your offer letter or your comp plan.

56
00:02:42.420 --> 00:02:46.380
If you ever have a question about what
applies to you, go there

57
00:02:46.380 --> 00:02:48.320
first or ask your manager.

58
00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:53.380
Alright, next up, what a real day actually
looks like here.

59
00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:54.680
How you run your

60
00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:57.420
day and how the team stays in sync.

61
00:02:58.060 --> 00:03:00.740
Then we'll close out with where you can go
from here.
